nd Scottish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Beuzeville-la-Giffard in Seine-Maritime, France, named with the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Boso</i> + <i>ville</i> ‘settlement’. The final element has been altered as a result of association with the common placename ending <i>-well</i> ‘spring, stream’. Some instances of   Bovill   may have the same origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Buswell","meanings":["English (Midlands): variant of   Boswell  , of Norman origin."]},{"name":"Bovill","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from any of several places in Normandy whose medieval forms share a similar range of variants, such as Bouville (Seine-Maritime), any of several places called Biéville (Calvados, Manche) or Biville (Manche, Seine-Maritime), Beuzeville-la-Giffard (Seine-Maritime), Boiville (Orne), and perhaps Boudeville (Seine-Maritime). See also   Boswell   and   Beville  ."]},{"name":"Biswell","meanings":["English (Buckinghamshire): possibly from a lost or unidentified place called with Old English <i>bēos</i> ‘coarse grass’ + <i>wella</i> ‘spring, stream’. Alternatively, a variant of   Boswell  ."]},{"name":"Bussell","meanings":["English: variant of   Boswell   (of Norman origin) or   Bissell   1."]},{"name":"Baswell","meanings":["Possibly Scottish: variant of   Boswell  ."]}]},{"name":"Ellena","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Either a variant of   Helena   or possibly a fanciful spelling of   Eleanor  , influenced by   Ellen ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellena Boswell was born in 1420. She married Matthew Bostock in 1438, in Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters."},"et":{"1420–1455":"1420–1455","1400–1510":"1400–1510","1439–Female":"1439–Surnud","1440–1493":"1440–1493","1452–1482":"1452–1482","1456–Female":"1456–Surnud","about 1439":"umbes 1439","1456":"1456","1455":"1455","1510"